element.name: Dun Laoghaire - West Pier by Bootle, Traditional Cache (1/1)
element.long-description:
This cache is located on the West Pier in Dun Laoghaire in South County Dublin. The town of Dun Laoghaire is pleasant enough, but the seafront area is most relaxing and scenic. The East Pier is the more popular and well kept of the two piers in Dun Laoghaire, but the West Pier has a peaceful charm to it. The views across Dublin Bay to Howth are worth the visit. Bring binoculars to fully enjoy the views. There are several transport links to the cache. It can be reached from the Salthill / Monkstown DART station, the 7, 46a and 75 buses, as well as the ferry from Holyhead!
The cache is a very small tupperware box (9cm x 9cm x 3cm), so please only bring small items.
The cache site might be difficult to find, so it might be worth printing the spoiler photo. Apologies for the long clue...
element.encoded-hints: 200ft [from the] abandoned house, [find a] stone [with a large] round man-made hole [and a] white quartz stripe. Look under the rocks [in front of this] stone.

2010-06-11T19:15:51Z : Found it by Simotaniously
Lovely walk took me a few mins to find. Nice spot. Put in a little fish.

2010-06-05T19:00:00Z : Found it by poohbear50
Lovely walk along the Pier on a warm, sunny day. Lots of yachts were out so it was a lovely sight. Found the cache then sat for awhile waching the yachts. On our way back from the cache we saw Stenaline boat sail out of the harbour and I got some very good photos of it sailing through the mouth of the harbour. TFTC

2010-06-05T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wild Rover
Brisk breeze and very sunny so lots of craft out - really nice to watch. Even got to watch Stena sailing and was very interested to watch the yachts moving to make passage for her. TFTC

2010-06-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by fmurphy
Without the photos I would have struggled, but found it easily with them. TFTC

2009-03-08T19:00:00Z : Found it by Mancunian Pyrocacher
yes I know I'm a bit late in logging this [:I], but my excuse is that as the UK is a lot busier than Eire cache wise. I've put my Geocaching time in publishing caches rather than log them [:D]
Me and my bright ideas. Oh we'll get to the Ferry Port early and do the local caches. It didn't look that long a walk on the map [:D]. But hey I dragged my weary legs there and back [8D]. Gave a cool finish to a great weekend
Dave

2007-08-23T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
The alternate coordinates in a previous log certainly helped in this one. As did the clue. We noted, being Aussies, that there was the perfect stubby holder...
